paragraphs.text:
%md

In this example we download the entire corpus of Shakespear's collected works, and run a simple word count in Apache Beam using both an Apache Spark and an Apache Flink Runner.

Even though we're a Flink Meetup, we do use Spark anytime we want to do anything against HDFS- this is primarily because the setup on this cluster Spark is configured to run with HDFS and Flink is not.  The two functions we use are simply utility- downloading data into HDFS and analyzing the results.

paragraphs.text:
%spark
val html = scala.io.Source.fromURL("https://ocw.mit.edu/ans7870/6/6.006/s08/lecturenotes/files/t8.shakespeare.txt").mkString
val list = html.split("\n").filter(_ != "")
val rdds = sc.parallelize(list, 1)
rdds.saveAsTextFile("/tmp/shakespeare1.txt")
paragraphs.title: Collect Data
